parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, loss of brakes, and loss of steering, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle stalls and loses brakes and steering when restarted.

rod bearing failure in the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Rear Brake Wear and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear and failure of the rear brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
A faulty brake caliper can cause the brakes to hang up, leading to overheating, smoke, and potentially a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
